  "word_type": "noun",
  "definition": "The context-dependent sense of whether a particular type of input (tentative, questioning, redirecting) counts as appropriate participation.",
  "etymology": "",
  "longer_description": "Different interaction framings create different boundaries around what kinds of contributions register as legitimate. In tool mode, only direct answers to stated questions feel appropriate; uncertainty, questions-back, or reframings feel like category errors. In collaboration, these become valid moves.",
  "example": "Asking 'why do you want to do this?' could be legitimate collaborative inquiry or presumptuous tool-overreach depending entirely on relational framing.",
